# Naming Conventions

## Files

- All component / demo / showcase files: **kebab-case** with `.jsx` extension.
  - Good: `border-beam.jsx`, `animated-list.jsx`
  - Bad: `BorderBeam.jsx`, `borderBeam.jsx`, `animated_list.jsx`

## Component exports (UI)

- The primary component export uses **PascalCase** matching the file name:
  - File `border-beam.jsx` exports `function BorderBeam(props) { … }`
- Sub-components stay in the same file using PascalCase:
  - `BentoGrid`, `BentoCard` (both in `bento-grid.jsx`)

## Demo variant exports

A demo file lives at `components/demo/.../<component>.jsx` and exports one or
more variants. Variant names follow:

- `<ComponentName>Demo` → the canonical default variant. Always present.
- `<ComponentName>DemoStart` → the smallest minimal example (props default).
- `<ComponentName>Demo<Modifier>` → variations, e.g.
  `BorderBeamDemoComponent`, `ConfettiDemoFireworks`, `LensDemoStatic`.

```jsx
// ✅ GOOD
export function BorderBeamDemo() { /* … */ }
export function BorderBeamDemoStart() { /* … */ }
export function BorderBeamDemoComponent() { /* … */ }

// ❌ BAD
export function BorderBeamStart() { /* … */ }      // missing "Demo"
export function BorderBeamDemo2() { /* … */ }      // numbered, not descriptive
export function borderBeamDemo() { /* … */ }      // lower camelCase
```

## Group folders

Use the official Magic UI group names: `components`, `special-effects`,
`animations`, `text`, `device`, `buttons`, `backgrounds`, `community`. Do not
invent new groups.

## index.js exports

Each `index.js` re-exports each file with `export * from './<name>'`. Keep them
sorted alphabetically when reasonable.
